_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     Create an R object that represents an HTML tag. For convenience,
     common HTML tags (e.g., <div>) can be created by calling for their
     tag name directly (e.g., ‘div()’). To create less common HTML5 (or
     SVG) tags (e.g., <article>), use the ‘tags’ list collection (e.g.,
     ‘tags$article()’). To create other non HTML/SVG tags, use the
     lower-level ‘tag()’ constructor.

